Hi
I'm 30 years old
I started coke at 20,
I never took everyday nor being super addict
I used to take some 1 or 2 times a month top, But since about 6 months and even 1 year I can't manage to control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even if before I was swearing to myself not to go pick up some snow , after 2 or 3 drinks I start to get heated and I tell myself "come on you have only one life let's gooo" and impossible to control myself too eager to take some
So here I know the problem is alcohol to begin with but it's almost impossible to stop with family with friends for pre-dinner drinks ect
Does anyone have this problem?
Thanks
stop drinking and the problem will be settled
sometimes you have to force yourself to stop ...
did you at least talk to your family doctor?
seeing an addictologist might make you feel better, especially to "assess" your consumption
Actually the hardest moment to hold up mentally is at night
during the day it's fine
Hello,
I'm a polyaddict with a big alcoholism prob,
I'm weaned off alcohol since a few years, but I can't convince myself I will never drink another drop of alcohol, since I want to, not enough will maybe,
sometimes I drink again on occasions bc its stronger than me and as soon as I start its impossible for me to stop,
afterwards I sleep rly bad and am sick the day after and above all I hate myself,
I'm ashamed, of who I become when I've been drinking and I suffer from it,
I can't drink normally
I drink all my glasses bottoms up,
why do I have this relationship with alcohol even though a lot of people can drink normally??
I haven't been drinking for 10 days,
this weekend I'm invited to a birthday and I'm very very afraid,
if you understand me leave the same thing or have gotten over it I take everything that can help me.
thank you for reading me and I'm waiting for your answers.
regards
